Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_rail_analysis_domain(25.10)                set_rail_analysis_domain(25.10)

Name
       set_rail_analysis_domain - Specifies a rail analysis power domain

Syntax
       set_rail_analysis_domain

       [-help]

       -name <domain_name>

       -pwrnets <power_net>_list

       -gndnets <ground_net_list>

       [-threshold <value>]

       Specifies a rail analysis power domain.

       Note: For a power-gated domain, you should only specify the "always on"
       net.  The  switched net should not be specified as part of power domain
       definition, because it is traced by the program automatically.

Parameters
       -gndnets <ground_net_list>
              Specifies a list of ground nets that are in the domain.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each set_rail_analysis_domain parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man set_rail_analysis_domain.

       -name<domain_name>
              Specifies the name of the power domain.

       -pwrnets<power_net_list>
              Specifies a list of power nets that are in the domain.

       -threshold <value>
              Specifies  the  minimum  allowed voltage on the power net or the
              maximum rise on the ground net, depending on the setting of the-
              voltage parameter. The -thresholdparameter  is  used  to  verify
              that  the  power grid passes the limit check and to set the fil-
              ters for an IR plot.

              Note: This parameter does not support domains  with  MSMV  power
              nets.

              If  you have specified both net (set_pg_nets -threshold) and do-
              main-based (set_rail_analysis_domain -threshold) thresholds, the
              net-based threshold will be honored.

              The valid value for threshold is between 0 and  0.5  (50%).  For
              example,  set_rail_analysis_domain -threshold 0.1 indicates that
              0.1 is 10% IRdrop. If a power net  in  the  domain  has  nominal
              voltage of 1v, 10% of threshold will translate to 100mV of maxi-
              mum effective IRdrop between the power and ground net.

Examples
              * The  following  command  sets the power domain TDSP to include
                VDD_TDSPCore_R and VSS nets:

                set_rail_analysis_domain -name  TDSP  -pwrnets  VDD_TDSPCore_R
                -gndnets VSS

